Calcium formations on ‘Altamura Man’ suggest he was 128,000 to 187,000 years old . 
  Now researchers plan to sequence his DNA to see if they can reveal new details about the evolution of our ancient ancestors . 
  The skeleton was found in a cave in southern Italy in 1993 . 
  Scientists in Italy have extracted the oldest ever DNA sample to be taken from a Neanderthal . 
 